The usual solution here is to leverage _polymorphism_ and progam to an interface, not an implementation. You have many classes all implement the same interface. Each implementation will do something different, but the method signature is identical. This allows you to swap the implementation, without affecting the callers.

```
interface HintProvider {
  Hint getHint(
      Map&lt;…, …&gt; numberMap,
      Board penBoard,
      Board pencilBoard,
      Board solvedBoard,
      Collection&lt;Hint&gt; hints)
}

class NakedSingle implements HintProvider {
  @Override
  public Hint getHint(
      final Map&lt;…, …&gt; numberMap,
      final Board penBoard,
      final Board pencilBoard,
      final Board solvedBoard,
      final Collection&lt;Hint&gt; hints) {
    // impl …
  }
}
```

